<definition id="fs-idm58337840">
<term>arbitrage</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm58302768">the process of buying a good and selling goods across borders to take advantage of international price differences</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm32629168">
<term>purchasing power parity (PPP)</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm38641888">the exchange rate that equalizes the prices of internationally traded goods across countries</meaning>
</definition>
